<item>
            <title>[THRIFT-1806] Python generation always truncates __init__.py files</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/THRIFT-1806</link>
                <project id="12310800" key="THRIFT">Thrift</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When generating python code the generator correctly creates _&lt;em&gt;init&lt;/em&gt;&lt;em&gt;.py file for each directory. If the __init&lt;/em&gt;_.py file has contents it is always overwritten. This usually isn&apos;t a problem unless using the -out flag, then there is a potential to erase non generated code.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
